name: Bogg_Tyrell
content:
Bogg Tyrell was an Aleena female from her species' homeworld, Aleen, which she represented in the Senate of the Galactic Republic. In 22 BBY, Tyrell piloted a speeder through the skylanes of Coruscant, capital of the Republic, while being entertained by the Dug holodrama star Seboca.
As they flew through traffic, Tyrell was forced to swerve out of the way to avoid colliding with the Jedi Knight Obi-Wan Kenobi, who was hanging from the assassin droid ASN-121. Tyrell cried out during the near miss, while Seboca cursed at Kenobi. Tyrell later entered Dex's Diner in the CoCo Town district of Coruscant while both Kenobi and Seboca were seated inside. She staggered out again soon after with a drink in hand. The senator had blue-and-tan skin, blue eyes, and wore a brown jacket over a red shirt with tan sleeves.
Bogg Tyrell appeared in the 2002 prequel trilogy film, Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones. The character was created by modifying the computer-generated model of podracer Ratts Tyerell made for the 1999 film Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace. In the current Star Wars canon, the character was first identified in "The Dual Worlds of Aleen," an article published in issue fifty-six of the Star Wars: Build the Millennium Falcon magazine series around January 27, 2016. The name was first used in the Star Wars Legends continuity in the 2003 reference book Inside the Worlds of Star Wars: Attack of the Clones, which was written by Simon Beecroft and Curtis Saxton.
